Parts cleaners are simple to operate. As shown in Fig. 15.2
, the degreasing solution is sprayed on the contaminated part through the nozzle located in the upper sink. The microbes and nutrients are introduced into the used degreasing solution in the lower tank where the microbes are activated and begin to digest the hydrocarbons in the solution. The clean solution is filtered to trap particulate matter and is recirculated to the upper sink where it can be used to clean additional parts. Heating elements in the lower tank maintain the operating temperature within a range that is ideal for the microbes to thrive, generally 323 to 360 K. The sink itself is also maintained clean (Fig. 15.3
).
